**Online Election System**

# 1\. Introduction

The Online Election System is a web-based application designed and developed by our team as part of our academic project. The primary objective of this project is to create a secure, efficient, and transparent platform for conducting elections. Our team aims to provide a user-friendly interface for voters, candidates, and administrators, while ensuring the integrity and accuracy of the electoral process. Throughout this document, we will outline the design and development of the Online Election System, including its functional and non-functional requirements, system architecture, and technical specifications.

# 2\. Product Vision

Our vision for the Online Election System is to create a reliable, accessible, and secure platform that empowers voters, candidates, and election administrators to participate in a transparent and efficient electoral process. We aim to make voting easier, faster, and more convenient, while ensuring the integrity and accuracy of the election results.

# 3\. Product Backlog

The Product Backlog consists of the following user stories and tasks:

## 3.1. Admin Login and Dashboard

\- As an administrator, I want to be able to log in to the system securely.

\- As an administrator, I want to be able to view a dashboard that displays key election metrics.

## 3.2. Candidate Registration and Document Verification

\- As a candidate, I want to be able to register for an election online.

\- As an administrator, I want to be able to verify candidate documents electronically.

## 3.3. Candidate Login and Profile Management

\- As a candidate, I want to be able to log in to the system securely.

\- As a candidate, I want to be able to view and edit my profile information.

## 3.4. Voter Registration and Login

\- As a voter, I want to be able to register for an election online.

\- As a voter, I want to be able to log in to the system securely.

## 3.5. Voting Mechanism and Result Calculation

\- As a voter, I want to be able to cast my vote online.

\- As an administrator, I want to be able to view election results in real-time.

## 3.6. System Security and Authentication

\- As an administrator, I want to be able to ensure that the system is secure and protected from unauthorized access.

\- As a voter, I want to be able to trust that my vote is secure and confidential.

## 3.7. User Interface and User Experience

\- As a user, I want to be able to navigate the system easily and intuitively.

\- As a user, I want to be able to view clear and concise instructions and feedback.

## 3.8. Deployment and Maintenance

\- As an administrator, I want to be able to deploy the system on a secure server.

\- As an administrator, I want to be able to perform regular maintenance and updates to ensure the system remains secure and functional.

# 5\. Technical Requirements

\- Front-end: HTML5, CSS3, JavaScript, ReactJS

\- Back-end: NodeJS, ExpressJS, MongoDB

\- Database: MongoDB

\- Security: OAuth, SSL/TLS, Encryption

\- Deployment: AWS, Docker

# 6\. Testing and Quality Assurance

To ensure our Online Election System is reliable, secure, and works as expected, we'll perform the following tests:

Unit Testing: We'll use Jest to test individual components and functions, making sure each part works correctly.

Integration Testing: Cypress will help us test how different components interact, ensuring the system works seamlessly from start to finish.

User Acceptance Testing (UAT): We'll conduct UAT to confirm the system meets stakeholders' requirements and expectations, gathering feedback and making necessary adjustments.

Code Review: Regular code reviews will ensure our code is readable, maintainable, and follows best practices, guaranteeing security and vulnerability-free code.

# 7\. Conclusion

In conclusion, the Online Election System is a secure and efficient web-based application that promotes transparency and accountability in the electoral process. Its adaptable and scalable design ensures the integrity of future elections.
